abstract: Law enforcement agents opened fire on an SUV driver who smashed through two security checkpoints at Mar-a-Lago on Friday in what authorities described as the actions of “an obviously impaired" driver but not an intentional attack on President Donald Trump's resort.
snippet: Law enforcement agents opened fire on an SUV driver who smashed through two security checkpoints at Mar-a-Lago on Friday in what authorities described as the actions of “an obviously impaired" driver but not an intentional attack on President Dona...
lead_paragraph: PALM BEACH, Fla. — Law enforcement agents opened fire on an SUV driver who smashed through two security checkpoints at Mar-a-Lago on Friday in what authorities described as the actions of “an obviously impaired" driver but not an intentional attack on President Donald Trump's resort.
headline_main: Police Open Fire at 'Impaired' Driver in Mar-a-Lago Breach
headline_print_headline: Police Open Fire at 'Impaired' Driver in Mar-a-Lago Breach

abstract: Toronto’s health care system fell into chaos and confusion during the SARS outbreak 17 years ago. Changes stemming from that crisis are now being tested.

abstract: A plan under discussion by Republican officials has not been completed and may merely be an effort to nudge weary senators toward a speedier conclusion.
snippet: A plan under discussion by Republican officials has not been completed and may merely be an effort to nudge weary senators toward a speedier conclusion.
lead_paragraph: The Senate’s impeachment trial of President Trump could continue into next week under a plan being discussed on Friday by Republican officials.
headline_main: The trial’s final verdict could be postponed until next week.

abstract: Senators will debate whether to seek additional witnesses and documents in President Trump’s trial. A vote is expected after they finish.

headline_main: Watch Live: Senators Debate Impeachment Trial Witnesses

abstract: The senator says the public will rebel if the Senate removed President Trump for merely “inappropriate” behavior.
snippet: The senator says the public will rebel if the Senate removed President Trump for merely “inappropriate” behavior.
lead_paragraph: Senator Lamar Alexander, Republican of Tennessee, who announced Thursday he would not support new witnesses in the impeachment trial of President Trump, said on Friday that he did not think the American public would accept Mr. Trump’s ouster if the Senate removed him.

abstract: President Donald Trump on Friday canceled an Obama-era prohibition on the use of anti-personnel landmines outside of the Korean peninsula. With potential future conflict with China and Russia in mind, the new policy specified no geographic limits on landmine use, declaring that the weapons offer an important war-fighting capability.
snippet: President Donald Trump on Friday canceled an Obama-era prohibition on the use of anti-personnel landmines outside of the Korean peninsula. With potential future conflict with China and Russia in mind, the new policy specified no geographic limits ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump on Friday canceled an Obama-era prohibition on the use of anti-personnel landmines outside of the Korean peninsula. With potential future conflict with China and Russia in mind, the new policy specified no geographic limits on landmine use, declaring that the weapons offer an important war-fighting capability.
headline_main: Trump Shifts to Authorize Wider US Military Use of Landmines
headline_print_headline: Trump Shifts to Authorize Wider US Military Use of Landmines

abstract: The letter did not take a position on whether President Trump should be removed from office.
snippet: The letter did not take a position on whether President Trump should be removed from office.
lead_paragraph: About 300 law professors and legal historians, in an open letter to the Senate on Friday,  rejected the arguments put forward by the Trump impeachment legal team. They explained that the scholarly consensus is that impeachment does not require proof of an indictable crime and that “abuse of power” is an impeachable offense, contrary to what President Trump’s team has broadly argued
headline_main: Scholars tell the Senate that Trump team’s legal arguments are wrong.

abstract: The Senate is debating whether to hear additional witnesses in President Trump’s trial.
snippet: The Senate is debating whether to hear additional witnesses in President Trump’s trial.
lead_paragraph: The newest revelations from the book by President Trump’s former national security adviser, John R. Bolton, put top aides in the room when Mr. Trump asked Mr. Bolton to help with his pressure campaign on Ukraine.

headline_main: Bolton says Trump’s aides heard the president ask him in the Oval Office to help pressure Ukraine.
byline_original: By Maggie Haberman and Michael S. Schmidt

abstract: The president asked his national security adviser last spring in front of other senior advisers to pave the way for a meeting between Rudolph Giuliani and Ukraine’s new leader.
snippet: The president asked his national security adviser last spring in front of other senior advisers to pave the way for a meeting between Rudolph Giuliani and Ukraine’s new leader.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — More than two months before he asked Ukraine’s president to investigate his political opponents, President Trump directed John R. Bolton, then his national security adviser, to help with his pressure campaign to extract damaging information on Democrats from Ukrainian officials, according to an unpublished manuscript by Mr. Bolton.
